00037 /**
00038  * \file sierradump.c
00039  * \brief Read a sierra input file and report it's content to standard output
00040  *
00041  * $Source: /usr/local/Repositories/fcdmf/fclib/tools/sierradump.c,v $
00042  * $Revision: 1.17 $ 
00043  * $Date: 2006/08/30 19:20:04 $
00044  *
00045  * \modifications
00046  *   - 2003-JUN-24  W Koegler Created to test new Sierra parser 
00047  */
00048 
00049 // C library includes
00050 #include <stdio.h>
00051 #include <stdlib.h>
00052 
00053 // fclib includes
00054 #include "base.h"
00055 #include "sierra.h"
00056 
00057 int main(int argc, char** argv) 
00058 {
00059   FC_ReturnCode rc; // return code
00060   char* filename;
00061   FC_SierraInfo* sierra;
00062 
00063   // Process arguments
00064   if (argc != 2) {
00065     printf("usage: sierradump <sierra_input_file>\n");
00066     fflush(NULL);
00067     exit(-1);
00068   }
00069   filename = argv[1];
00070 
00071   // do it
00072   rc = fc_parseSierraInputFile(filename, &sierra);
00073   if (rc != FC_SUCCESS) {
00074     printf("fc_parseSierraInputFile returned error: '%s'\n", 
00075            fc_getReturnCodeText(rc));
00076     fflush(NULL);
00077     exit(rc);
00078   }
00079   rc = fc_printSierraInfo(sierra);
00080   if (rc != FC_SUCCESS) {
00081     printf("fc_printSierraInfo returned error: '%s'\n", 
00082            fc_getReturnCodeText(rc));
00083     fflush(NULL);
00084     exit(rc);
00085   }
00086 
00087   // cleanup
00088   fc_freeSierraInfo(sierra);
00089 
00090   exit(0);
00091 }
